		"title": "USN-4047-1 -- libvirt vulnerabilities",
		"description": "Matthias Gerstner and JÃ¡n Tomko discovered that libvirt incorrectly handled certain API calls. An attacker could possibly use this issue to check for arbitrary files, or execute arbitrary binaries. In the default installation, attackers would be isolated by the libvirt AppArmor profile.  Update Instructions:  Run `sudo pro fix USN-4047-1` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected by updating your system to the following package versions:  libvirt0 - 1.3.1-1ubuntu10.27 libvirt-dev - 1.3.1-1ubuntu10.27 libvirt-doc - 1.3.1-1ubuntu10.27 libvirt-bin - 1.3.1-1ubuntu10.27 No subscription required",
